      "link": null,
      "locked": false,
      "text": "The basics of btree index\nB-tree indexes are the default index type in PostgreSQL.They are created automatically \nfor primary key and unique constraints.",
      "fontSize": 36,
      "fontFamily": 6,
      "textAlign": "left",
      "verticalAlign": "top",
      "containerId": null,
      "originalText": "The basics of btree index\nB-tree indexes are the default index type in PostgreSQL.They are created automatically \nfor primary key and unique constraints.",
      "autoResize": true,
      "lineHeight": 1.25
    },
    {
      "id": "W89s20G1d5s_dAwUsPrvA",
      "type": "text",
      "x": 4956.103308351913,
      "y": 4458.107438624094,
      "width": 1737.0711669921875,
      "height": 135,
      "angle": 0,
      "strokeColor": "#e03131",
      "backgroundColor": "transparent",
      "fillStyle": "hachure",
      "strokeWidth": 4,
      "strokeStyle": "solid",
      "roughness": 1,
      "opacity": 100,
      "groupIds": [],
      "frameId": null,
      "index": "b1U",
      "roundness": null,
      "seed": 1339204788,
      "version": 5,
      "versionNonce": 890284724,
      "isDeleted": false,
      "boundElements": null,
      "updated": 1762743895282,
      "link": null,
      "locked": false,
      "text": " Indexes are also stored physically separate from the data structures, with leaf node pages typically storing\n the key and a tuple identifier\n (pointer) to the data row in the heap",
      "fontSize": 36,
      "fontFamily": 6,
      "textAlign": "left",
      "verticalAlign": "top",
      "containerId": null,
      "originalText": " Indexes are also stored physically separate from the data structures, with leaf node pages typically storing\n the key and a tuple identifier\n (pointer) to the data row in the heap",
      "autoResize": true,
      "lineHeight": 1.25
    },
